At the 2023 ANS Annual Meeting in Indianapolis, IN, several members of ART presented their research.
David Kang presented two summaries, entitled &ldquo;Flow Regime Classification Using Orientation-Independent Layered Spectral Clustering&rdquo; and &ldquo;RGB Mapping: A Dynamic Approach for Flow Pattern Identification and Classification&rdquo;
Adam Dix presented a &ldquo;One-Dimensional Drift Flux Analysis of Bubbly Flows in Horizontal and Inclined-Upward Orientations&rdquo;, on behalf of co-authors ART alum Dr. Drew Ryan and Dr. Seungjin Kim

   From Left to Right: David Kang, Adam Dix, and Zhengting Quan   At the 2023 ANS Annual Meeting in Indianapolis, IN, several members of ART presented their research.
  Ph.D. student David Kang presents his research   David Kang presented his summary, titled &ldquo;A Direct Comparison of Flow Visualization and Machine Learning for Inclined Two-Phase Flow Regime Identification&rdquo;
  Ph.D. student Zhengting Quan presents his research   Zhengting Quan presented his research, titled &ldquo;Numerical Investigations of the Single-Phase Flow Characteristics in U-Bends&rdquo;
Additionally, ART alum Dr. Drew Ryan presented a paper titled &ldquo;Improving Multiphase CFD Closure Models for Horizontal Bubbly Two-Phase Flow&rdquo;, co-authored with Adam Dix and Dr. Seungjin Kim

At the 2022 ANS Winter Meeting in Phoenix, AZ, several members of ART presented their research.
Drew Ryan presented research titled &ldquo;Evaluation of Computational Fluid Dynamic Models for Bubbly Two-Phase Flows in Inclined Upward Orientations&rdquo;
  Masters student David Kang presents his research   David Kang presented his research, titled &ldquo;Flow Regime Identification for Inclined Two-Phase Flows using Machine Learning&rdquo;
  PhD student Adam Dix presents his research   Adam Dix presented work related to his Masters&rsquo; thesis, titled &ldquo;Evaluation of Pressure Drop Models for 7-Pin Wire-Wrapped Rod Bundles&rdquo;
